A Mother Ten Years in the Past 
It was a day ten years ago . The teacher was using the lunch break to nap at home , when suddenly the telephone rang . 
She answered and heard an unfamiliar rough voice from the receiver : " Your child stole a book and we caught her . Come over right away ! " 
The crying of a little girl could also be heard though the receiver , as well as the sound of somebody nearby scolding her . 
She turned her head to look at her only daughter watching the television and then immediately understood what was happening . 
Clearly , a little girl had been caught by a store clerk stealing a book and did not want her family to find out , so she dialed a number at random and happened to call there . 
Of course , she could hang up and forget about it , or even reprimand the party on the other line , 
because this affair had absolutely nothing to do with her . 
But she was a teacher , and it could be that it was one of her students . 
Through the telephone , she could roughly imagine that the little girl who had made a mistake on the spur of the moment was surely terrified , since she was facing what could be life 's most frightening circumstance . 
After hesitating a moment , a thought suddenly came to her mind . Yes , she would do it . 
Thereupon , after asking the bookstore 's address , she rushed over there . 
Just as she had anticipated , standing in the bookstore was a little girl with a face full of tears . 
The adults beside her were ferociously and loudly scolding her . 
She instantly rushed forward and gathered the pitiful little girl into her arms , then turned toward the nearby store clerk and said : " Whatever you have to say you can say to me . You shouldn 't frighten children . " 
During the muttering of the somewhat unwilling store clerk , she paid the fine of less than one hundred yuan and then , with the little girl in hand , walked out of the store where she could see clearly the face overwhelmed by panic and tears . 
She smiled and returned home with the little girl where she tidied her up without asking anything , then let the little girl leave , 
As the little girl was about to go , she also made a point of urging , " If you want to read a book , then come here to Auntie 's house . There are lots of books here . ' 
The still badly shaken little girl looked are her deeply for a moment , then dashed off , after which she never came back . 
Time rushed by like running water . Imperceptibly , ten years went by in a flash . 
She had forgotten the incident , still living there as before , she led a calm and peaceful life . 
One afternoon , there was a knocking on the outside door . 
Opening the door to her apartment , she saw a pretty young woman she did not know . The girl was smiling broadly and in her hands she held a stack of presents . 
" Who are you looking for ? " 
she asked with uncertainty . 
The young girl excitedly gave a long explanation . 
To her surprise , from the unfamiliar young lady 's story she suddenly realized that the young woman was actually the little girl from that year . Ten years later , she had graduated from university without difficulty and had now come especially to call on her . 
The young woman 's eyes glistened with tears as she said in a gentle voice : " Although I still don 't understand even today why you were willing to pass yourself off as my mother and come to my rescue , but for the last ten years I had a constant feeling that I wanted to cry out ' Mother ' to you . " 
The teacher 's eyes started to cloud over as well . 
Somewhat curious , she asked : " If I hadn 't helped you that day , what would have been the result ? " 
The young woman 's face instantly darkened and she lightly shook her head , saying : " I 'm not sure . Maybe I would have gone on doing stupid things , or I might even have died . " 
A violent shiver went through the teacher 's heart , then she rejoiced to herself . 
The impetuous decision that she had made back then had unexpectedly had such an influence on a person 's entire life . 
Looking at the happy smile on the young woman 's face , she also began to smile . 
